annotation.TEXT: So anyway, it looks like getting all of the stars during the boss fight will be a thing, especially the highest stars towards the right side.
Okay, quick, finish her!
Marisa's already getting impatient...
Oh! Now's my chance!
Aw, the waiting game sucks. Let's play Hungry Hungry Hippos!
Okay, so those 41 stars I already collected weren't too tough to get, but those 2 stars down there are another story altogether.
Alright, just 3 tricky stars left to go!
This opening room just appears to be an empty room with a pipe, but it scrolls up, so maybe I come back here with a broom to get some high-up stars?
However, I have no other method to deal with the Chomps in this room here, and I can afford to give up a portion of my 500 seconds.
Oh, what the heck! I totally drill stomped there! But, the game must've decided that I hit the ground first, and thus wasn't drill stomping when I hit the knife. I hate that glitch.
Oh, man! What an epic escape!
Yes! Now I just have to win without dying!
Yep, I just drill stomped the pointy end of that one. Fortunately, direction the knife points doesn't matter. All that matters is that I hit it from above while drill stomping.
I like leaving at least one brick there for most of the battle, so that I can jump off of it if needed.
There's many potato chips up above.
Oh, and I don't know why I didn't take a mulligan like I usually do when my first life ends very early, but whatever.
Alright, let's begin world 4-1-4, which is going to be another boss level!
So, let's wait a while and see if these Chomps will indeed eventually break their chains in this game if you wait long enough...
And somehow, I managed to escape that corner there.
It's like the Potted Ghost boss from Yoshi's Island, and you have to push this block that Sakuya is chained to all the way into the pit on the right.
All of the other stars in this room can be gotten with skill and patience, waiting for the Chomps to lunge in a direction that allows you to get by.
Of course, hugging the far left wall always keeps you safe from the lunge, but beware of the knives, and try not to let yourself get trapped in the lower-left corner.
Okay, good. I got 2 of the remaining stars that way. Still 7 to go...
Alright, now I've gotta go for the perfect...
Now, understandably, the stars on the top row towards the right side are indeed the hardest ones to get, and do require that you jump off of Sakuya's block.
So, let me just work my way over there, after I'm done collecting these stars that I don't need.
Bouncing off of that Chomp down there is one way to reach this high ledge, but jumping from the ledge on the right also works.
They're in a cramped space and guarded by Chomps on both sides, so how could I possibly reliably get them without dying?
I think this is the best start to the boss fight that I've had, so I hope it doesn't go to waste! (Game, please don't crash on me again...)
Whoa, narrow escape there. Now, I'm pretty sure I can jump off of Sakuya's block to reach the highest stars over there, but I'll have to dodge her head and the knives.
27 attempts later... (13 fails on the pre-boss room, 14 fails on Sakuya.)
And there goes the second one! Now I can get these 2 stars much more easily! Be careful, since the other Chomps nearby might also break free if you take too long.
Hello, and welcome back to Super Marisa World! You may be wondering what I'm doing back here in this part of 4-1-3. Well, I've decided to show off pipe #3.
No, I don't. Have you tried looking for her yourself?
For the Chomp in the upper-right, just wait until he lunges in a direction that allows you to get the stars he's guarding and then get out.
Hello, and welcome back to Super Marisa World! ...Wait, didn't I already say that? Well, I'm saying it again anyway!
There's our usual ominous music, and... Oh... pudding... no...
Why the heck do I look like this!?
For the stars above the second Chomp here, just drill stomp bounce off of him while he's stationary from lunging. It's not quite as hard as it looks.
Whatever, this still sucks.
Alright, it's boss time! Now, I do remember from raocow's playthrough what you're supposed to do here.
Oh, man. She's doing consecutive time stops.
Watch out for the blue potato chips here, and when you enter the pipe, DO NOT immediately charge to the right! Instead, going left or jumping immediately is advised!
Oh, so close! I thought I could get all three there! Still, that's more progress, and now only one tricky star remains!
I decided to return to normal speed here so you can get a better look at this Chomp breaking his chain.
ARGH!!! I couldn't retreat to the left fast enough that time, and I failed to jump over her lunge.
Now she's doing some time-stopping, but I can escape by using that brick I left intact!
This sure is fitting for the devil's lap dog.
Yeah, that's probably what I'll need to do in order to be able to reach the stars up there. But, I'm obviously not going to worry about stars on this run.
Now, in SMB3, it's really not terribly useful, since it takes well over 100 seconds, and most levels only give you 300, and there are usually other ways to deal with them.
Ugh, I jumped right into that one. Well, I'm on my last life, but I've almost won.
Oh, and hoping that the knife isn't close enough to the ground that I get glitch-killed due to the game thinking I hit the ground first.
And that's why. That stupid white duder. Definitely very cheap enemy placement. Okay, after staving off that guy, there's a checkpoint and a bunch of clouds and platforms.
Oh, nice! I was able to get the rightmost top row stars there!
More importantly, know anything about Patchouli?
Alright, it's boss time, yet again!
To be continued... Ze!
And with that, I have now 100%-ed 28 out of the (I think) 56 levels in this game! So, I'm halfway done! Of course, I'm sure the remaining levels are just going to get harder...
The game's trying its darndest to trap me here.
Uh, oh. Two consecutive time stops followed by a lunge!
Yeah! Sakuya down! (I stopped like one pixel short for a split-second there. That would've been silly if I had lost due to that somehow.)
Alright, now for Sakuya. I like to start by quickly jumping up for some of the stars in the top-center of the room like that.
Whoa, geez! I saw that coming! Fortunately, she can't reach all the way to the left when she lunges like that.
Oh, and you didn't think I'd forget about that one star in the brick right there, did you?
And there he goes! Yep, the chain breaks about 5 seconds after it starts flashing, and the dude will aim straight at your position when that happens.
Uh, oh. I might've just gotten myself cornered here...
Well, in SMB3, there's a lesser-known trick, where if you just stay put and watch a Chomp for a long time (I think I heard someone say it takes 50 lunges)...
You know what, I think it crashed because Sakuya used time stop while there were no knives present (since I despawned 'em all), and the game divided by 0 or something.
Yikes! I can still retreat to the left, though!
Guess I'd better make you let me.
Note that when Sakuya decides to lunge, she'll aim at the height where you were at the time she made that decision. So, dodging vertically is certainly possible.
Yeah, the pre-boss room is that ridiculous. There are two stars in particular that are much more ridiculous than the others, and I'll point them out when I get to them.
Gah! That one took me completely by surprise!
As usual, misdirect the knives when time stop occurs. (Isn't Sakuya the one that should be using "Misdirection" on me?)
Sometimes, she takes her sweet time with deciding to lunge, and on one of my failed attempts, the timer did drop below 100 (I died to something else there, though).
You can jump from the red platform or bounce off the Rex to get above the pipes here, but I'm going to stay down low.
And now, back to our regularly scheduled adventure.
Sometimes, she'll time her special moves in such a way that screws me over. For instance, she might lunge while my escape routes are blocked by knives.
Come on, do another lunge already...
Just a little longer. Pay close attention to the Chomp on the left down there.
And now, we play the waiting game...
GOOOOOAAAAALLLLL!!!!!
Okay, this is about as far as I had gotten before, and this is the first time I got here with the broom. Anything further to the right?
Alright, let's finish her! But still be careful, as I've already had a couple of failures when I was really close to victory!
...the Chomp's chain will eventually break and the Chomp will go flying off. After this happens, you're free to safely get at whatever the Chomp used to be guarding.
Whew, I think I got lucky there. I might've been in trouble if she had decided to time-stop right at that moment.
Just a little further...
This pre-boss room is loaded with Chomps! I really hope there's a miko suit or something in here...
Ha. I knew that lunge was coming there since I didn't hear her start throwing more knives or begin charging up another time stop.
WHAT?! You've gotta be squidding me! And this run was looking promising, too...
Oh, there is something! This pipe down here! Somehow, I never noticed it on my previous passes through this area, and always doubled back too soon.
Well, I saw enough to know that there are no power ups here, so I'm just going to skip all the stars and go straight to the boss, who I imagine will be Chomp-like somehow.
Of course, since this is Sakuya, there's knives and time-stopping to deal with. It looks like all knives present are pointed at my current position during the time stop.
Watch out. If a Chomp on the lower level lunges straight up, it looks like it might just barely be able to hit you while you're on this ledge. (Don't know if that's true, though.)
And there you go. It was indeed just another way to get to the normal exit, but it's totally pointless, as I think pipe #1 is easier, and pipe #2 is the only way to get all the stars.
Alright, there's the "3", and the pipe to enter is up above. (The lower pipe with the green guy can't be entered.)
Game crash count: 2
Also, when you hear the time stop charging up, you can try to maneuver yourself to lead the knives in a direction that's easier for you to deal with.
There we go, and apparently, drill stomping her head is okay, albeit risky.
There are limited opportunities to do this safely though. I've had the best luck going for them immediately after a lunge, when there are few/no knives in the way.
Oh, this is the biggest transformation yet.
Oh, while I'm on the left and she's far to the right like this, I think the knives she's trying to summon are despawning immediately.
Ooh, freeze-frame on a drill stomp! Nice!
Also, be aware that a Chomp that breaks free isn't considered dead, so it might respawn in its original position with a fresh chain if you go far away and come back.
7 attempts later... (All Sakuya fails.) Alright, ludicrous speed time!
Well, it shouldn't be too long now. At the speed I typically go through this room, the thing I'm waiting for usually happens when the timer is in the 380s.
Aha, his chain is flashing! It's about to break! Step away and be ready to dodge!
So, next time, I'll be playing 4-2-1!
Holy pudding! What the heck?! Sakuya, what's happened to you?!
